// MFQ3 Training Mission 8 - Sea Run
// SEA waypoint course: sail the patrol boat (vehicle index 57) through a string
// of buoys on mfq3_subpen's open water. Checkpoints are Type sea, so they snap
// down to the waterline (MASK_WATER) - the .mis only needs rough X/Y. Same engine
// as the air gate (mission 6) and land marker (mission 7) courses, with a buoy
// marker instead of a ring/flag.
//
// CLOSE TEST course, due EAST. Screenshots showed the spawn pocket is bounded by
// shore to the NE (the old NE staircase beached its last buoys), but the boat
// freely sailed the corridor due east at Y~1660 from X~5848 out to X~6582 - all
// open water. So the buoys now step east along that verified-water line, ~200u
// apart starting ~250u ahead, and the spawn faces east (yaw 0) straight down it.
// Buoys auto-snap to the waterline. (Buoy sits a touch high + no boat-HUD radar
// blip yet - follow-ups once pass/ding/complete is confirmed.)
Overview
{
	map	mfq3_subpen
	gameset	2
	gametype	0
	mission	"Sea Run"
	goal	Waypoints
	order	8
	description	"Sail the patrol boat through every buoy."
	briefing	"Welcome to the water. You're at the helm of a patrol boat. A line of buoys marks a course around the harbour - the on-screen radar blip points at your next one. Throttle up, sail through each buoy in order, and mind the turning circle - boats don't stop on a dime. Clear all the buoys to pass."
	success	"Course complete - fine seamanship, skipper!"
	failure	"You're dead in the water before finishing. Come about and run it again."
}
Entities
{
	PlayerStart
	{
		Index	57
		Origin	5704.0;1696.0;64.0
		Angles	0.0;0.0;0.0
		Speed	0
	}
}
